  "problem": "The lifecycle lane already proved public response semantics on menu/combo surfaces that return `ResponseExt` or `ComboResponse`, but helper-owned menu/submenu/tab triggers used to collapse their internal trigger state into `bool open` or no outward return. This lane closes with an additive helper-level verdict: `begin_menu_response[_with_options]` and `begin_submenu_response[_with_options]` return `DisclosureResponse`, `tab_bar_response[_with_options]` returns `TabBarResponse`, and legacy wrappers stay intact without reopening richer menu/tab policy or widening `fret-authoring::Response`.",
